  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preparation Of The National Strategic Action Plan (Nsap) Of The Spatial Development Framework (Sdf) For Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This
project is a follow-up of the UN-Habitat-led Achieving Sustainable Urban
Development (ASUD) programme in Rwanda, which resulted with the formulation of
the NUP. The Spatial Development Framework (SDF) is a policy action of the NUP adopted
end of 2015. The completion of the SDF by elaborating the NSAP will allow its
approval ideally at cabinet level, which will increase the Government ownership
and also enhance the implementation of the NUP. 



The
analytical phase to prepare the SDF was carried out by UN-Habitat, so this
project is a natural continuation of this important assignment and the fact
that UN-Habitat possesses the required skills and expertise for it. It is
worthy to note that UN-Habitat prepared the SDF in three other countries,
namely Darfur in Sudan, Mozambique and Myanmar.</narrative>
  </description>
